$ Browser Object Model: window.getComputedStyle

`window.getComputedStyle(elem)` returns a `CSSStyleDeclaration` object that can be queried for
→ development/web/CSS[CSS] style values of an → development/web/HTML element.

The following example queries a few CSS values for the → development/web/HTML/tags/body[`<body`].

Since there is no explicit CSS set for this element, it prints the «default» values.

gh|Browser-Object-Model|/window/getComputedStyle.html||

When run in a browser, the above HTML document might print:
gh|Browser-Object-Model|/window/getComputedStyle.png||

sa:
  → development/web/browser/object-model/window[The window object]
